description.narrative: Nigeria expanded the delivery of immunization services into hard-to-reach areas through routine immunization intensification and supplemental immunization activities. ;DHIS2 ;documented Penta3 coverage of 77% ( January to October 2021) for under one infant, ;vs a 60% ;target; however data quality is questionable, ;and actual coverage could be lower. The annual penta3 target for LGAs with 80% was set at 31% and Nigeria achieved 43% ;(DHIS2). Nigeria has introduced ;IPV2 vaccine and has rolled out the covid 19 vaccine despite inadequate delivery capacities/ suboptimal demand. ; | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/01/2022
